As we build using a non-system CLang (due to DD having a dependency on a
version older than we've ever built), it isn't in the hardcoded paths that
rules_go sets in [0].  7.79 moved to using rules_go for the parts of the build
which require CLang, so we need to inject it back into PATH.

[0] https://github.com/bazel-contrib/rules_go/blob/9667748a32de210cd4a813b15e9d987103ba0954/go/private/context.bzl#L981

diff --git a/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl b/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
index 21f462db..657e2878 100644
--- a/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
+++ b/bazel/rules/ebpf/cgo_godefs.bzl
@@ -95,6 +95,8 @@ def _cgo_godefs_impl(ctx):
     )
 
     env = dict(go.env)
+    # PATH is no longer inherited from the environment, so we need to extend it here
+    env["PATH"] = ":".join(["/opt/clang/bin", env["PATH"]])
     env["CGO_ENABLED"] = "1"
 
     # run_shell needed: genpost reads stdin and writes stdout, so the pipeline
